<div dir="ltr">I&#39;ve run tonight&#39;s v1.7 tarball through most of my test platforms.<div>At this point I am aware of only 2 significant issues which I can reproduce:</div><div><br></div><div>1) At least open64 and pathscale &quot;regress&quot; with respect to mpif08 bindings (were not built in 1.7.3, but 1.7.4 is trying and failing to build them).  One can manually disable f08 binding to avoid the issue.</div>
<div><br></div><div>2) At least one ppc32 platform fails to link.  This is (blocker) ticket #4143 and I&#39;ve confirmed that the fix proposed there works for my test platform.</div><div><br></div><div>-Paul<br clear="all">
